statements.sql:
select count(*) as aggregate from `personal` left join (
SELECT
pers_id,
sum(d0) as d0,sum(d1) as d1,sum(d2) as d2,sum(d3) as d3,sum(d4) as d4,sum(d5) as d5,sum(d6) as d6,sum(d7) as d7,sum(d8) as d8,sum(d9) as d9
FROM (
SELECT
pers_id,
IF(date = 2018-07-02, sum, null) as d0,IF(date = 2018-07-03, sum, null) as d1,IF(date = 2018-07-04, sum, null) as d2,IF(date = 2018-07-05, sum, null) as d3,IF(date = 2018-07-06, sum, null) as d4,IF(date = 2018-07-07, sum, null) as d5,IF(date = 2018-07-08, sum, null) as d6,IF(date = 2018-07-09, sum, null) as d7,IF(date = 2018-07-10, sum, null) as d8,IF(date = 2018-07-11, sum, null) as d9
FROM (
SELECT
sum(worktime) as sum,
pers_id,
date
FROM personal_times
WHERE date BETWEEN '2018-07-02' AND '2018-07-11'
GROUP BY pers_id, date
) as pt
) as st
group by pers_id) as at on `at`.`pers_id` = `personal`.`pers_id` where `is_active` = '1' group by `personal`.`id`
